Action 1: Perform the "open" action to open the boot. 

Action 2 - 5: Perform the "fetch" action four times to get the jack, pump, wrench, and one intact tyre. 

Action 6: Perform the "inflate" action to inflate the intact tyre. 

Action 7: Perform the "fetch" action to take one flat tyre. 

Action 8: Perform the "loosen" action to loosen the nut on the hub of the flat tyre. 

Action 9: Perform the "jack-up" action to lift the hub off the ground. 

Action 10: Perform the "undo" action to undo the fastening of the nut on the hub. 

Action 11: Perform the "remove-wheel" action to remove the flat tyre from the hub. 

Action 12: Perform the "put-on-wheel" action to put the inflated tyre on the hub. 

Action 13: Perform the "do-up" action to fasten the nut on the hub. 

Action 14: Perform the "jack-down" action to lower the hub to the ground. 

Action 15: Perform the "tighten" action to tighten the nut on the hub. 

Action 16 - 19: Perform the "put-away" action four times to put the flat tyre, wrench, jack, and pump back in the boot.

Action 20: Perform the "close" action to close the boot. 

Repeat Actions 1-20 for each of the remaining 16 hubs and tyres. 

This plan guarantees that all flat tyres are replaced with inflated intact tyres, all necessary tools are put back in the boot, and the boot is closed, successfully achieving your goal.